gui.model.application

Class Application

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Observable
      • gui.model.application.observable.AppObservable
        • gui.model.application.Application

  • public class Application
extends AppObservable
    Application class encapsualtes the target application. Each application has one or more scenes (windows, dialogs, pages) and a name.
    On an application, some actions can be performed by a user. The result is a sequence of events, which can be stored in this class.
    Author:
    Michaela Bacikova, Slovakia, michaela.bacikova@tuke.sk

      • contains

        public boolean contains(Scene<?> scene)
        Two scenes are equal only if their scene components are equal The list of scenes contains the specified scene only if there is the same scene component in the list. The method returns true if the list of this applications' scenes contains the specified scene (scene component).
        Parameters:
        scene - the scene whose presence in this application should be tested
        Returns:
        true if the specified scene is present in this application, false otherwise
